<controls:ChildWindow x:Class="TheS.Casinova.TwoWins.Views.HowToPlayWindow"
           xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation" 
           xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml" 
           xmlns:controls="clr-namespace:System.Windows.Controls;assembly=System.Windows.Controls"
           Width="600" Height="400" 
           Title="How to play." FontSize="21.333">
    <Grid x:Name="LayoutRoot" Margin="2">
        <Grid.RowDefinitions>
            <RowDefinition />
            <RowDefinition Height="Auto" />
        </Grid.RowDefinitions>

        <Button x:Name="CloseButton" Content="Close" Click="CloseButton_Click" Width="75" Height="23" HorizontalAlignment="Right" Margin="0,12,0,0" Grid.Row="1" FontSize="11" />
        <Grid>
        	<RichTextBox FontSize="11" IsReadOnly="True">
        		<Paragraph>
        			<Run Text="Game: Two Wins" FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="12"/>
<LineBreak/><LineBreak/>
<Run Text="Standard Rules" FontWeight="Bold"/><LineBreak/>
- Each game period last 12 hours, with 1 hour "Critical Time Period" during the last hour.<LineBreak/>
- Each player has an infinite number of hands on which to place their bets. For each hand, players may place any number of whole-dollar bets.<LineBreak/>
- Players may increase the amount of the bet in any of their hands as many times as they want, at any time before the critical time period occurs.<LineBreak/>
- Players may neither decrease nor withdraw the amount of a bet in any of their hands during gameplay.<LineBreak/>
- The bets each player places will be updated in the Main Pot in real time.<LineBreak/>
- During a "Critical Time Period," each player may only update each of their hands once.<LineBreak/>
* The bets on new hands within the "Critical Time Period" will not be available until the "critical time period" elapses.<LineBreak/>

<LineBreak/><LineBreak/>
<Run Text="Information Shown (In real time)" FontWeight="Bold"/><LineBreak/>
- Remaining Time<LineBreak/>
- Main Pot (the amount of the Main Pot will be frozen once a "Critical Time Period" occurs)<LineBreak/>
- Name of the player winning the Low Bet, and the value of his winning bet<LineBreak/>
- Name of the player winning the High Bet, and the value of his winning bet<LineBreak/>
- Number of betting hands played in the game<LineBreak/>

<LineBreak/><LineBreak/>
<Run Text="Winners" FontWeight="Bold"/><LineBreak/>
- High Bet winner is the person who, in any hand, places the highest number of one-hand non-duplicate-amount* of bets in the pot.<LineBreak/>
- Low Bet winner is the person who, in any hand, places the lowest number of one-hand non-duplicate-amount* of bets in the pot.<LineBreak/>
*The winning hand must be the only hand in the game with such amount.  In case there is no non-duplicate-amount (more than 1 winner), the game will choose whomever placed the bet first as a winner.<LineBreak/>

<LineBreak/><LineBreak/>
<Run Text="Payouts" FontWeight="Bold"/><LineBreak/>
- If the highest one-hand non-duplicate-amount was placed before the "Critical Time Period," then The High Bet Winner takes 70% of the money from the Main Pot of that game.<LineBreak/>
- However, in a case where the highest one-hand non-duplicate-amount was updated or placed during the "Critical Time Period," then the High Bet Winner takes 50% of the money from the Main Pot of that game.<LineBreak/>
  The 20% reduction in this instance will be awarded to the Player who placed the highest one-hand non-dupicate-amount before the "Critical Time Period."<LineBreak/>
- If the lowest one-hand non-duplicate-amount was placed before the "Critical Time Period," then The Low Bet Winner takes 25% of the money from the Main Pot of that game.<LineBreak/>
- However, in the cast where the lowest one-hand non-duplicate-amount was updated or placed during the "Critical Time Period," then the Low Bet Winner takes 20% of the money from the Main Pot of that game.<LineBreak/>
  The 5% reduction in this instance will be given to the Player who placed the lowest one-hand non-dupicate-amount before the "Critical Time Period."<LineBreak/>


    		
				</Paragraph>
        	</RichTextBox>
        </Grid>
    </Grid>
</controls:ChildWindow>